body:
Sailor Moon Sticker Cards, Pokémon cards + Topps + stickers, Avatar cards, Dinosaur king arcade, Card Captor and Yu-gi-oh! cards

Hello, sorry for the trouble.

Y'see, I am getting a Paypal and whatnot soon and am planning on trying to sell on my old collection of sailor moon sticker, pokémon cards, Pokemon stickers, dinosaur king arcade cards, Card Captor, Bakugan(Not many, mostly the magnetic ones), Yu-Gi-Oh! and Avatar cards and need advice on if I should sell it as a set, individually and for how much for the lot/each and where to sell them on. (Additionally I have several unopened pokémon figurines, Pokémon metal tags, Japanese pokemon wind-up toys (Unused and in original packaging), Pokémon collector’s coins in mint condition, plushies(Going through washing and getting some TLC) and walkthrough guides (Although some of the guides are not in the best condition.))

Would also like advice on judgement of condition if not mint.

If anybody is interested then please drop a message and hopefully I can keep in touch to let you know what’s up and when (Could be a few weeks to a few months depending on when I can ship, when account is open and how much time I have), anybody experienced in selling this kind of thing is welcome.

If not selling them I would at least like some advice on where I can clear them out. (I am UK based)

(If replies are slow, I’m most likely at work but will get to you ASAP, Sorry for the trouble)

Thanks for reading!

Reviewing my personal opinion on every single Pokemon! Yes, all 809 of them!
(Mostly) Daily Uploads, 3 PM EST.

summary: Let’s Talk About Pokemon - Scraggy and Scrafty
title: Let’s Talk About Pokemon - Scraggy and Scrafty
body:
559: Scraggy

Now this is a Pokemon that pretty much only exists because of the age it was created in, being the late 2000s. There’s certainly a lot that could’ve been done with a lizard Pokemon themed around the shedding of its skin, but it’s all the more brilliant that Scraggy in particular picks up the look of a delinquent young teenager using its shed skin as baggy, sagging pants. And as someone that was in high school during Gen 5, that only made this line all the more hilarious to me. Seeing how I saw classmates that wore big, baggy pants far more than I’d care to admit. Yeah, 16-year-old white kids were mocking Pokemon about constantly. But little did they know there was a Pokemon mocking them too. HAH.

Personal Score: 9/10

And that’s too fun a design not to admire.

560: Scrafty

Then comes in Scrafty, who very thankfully doesn’t drop a single lovable attribute about Scraggy. Now even wearing a funky mohawk, and having Scraggy’s skin too! That hood around its neck looks just like Scraggy’s face, even complete with eyeholes. Scrafty’s just an absolutely fun design that doesn’t feel like it has too much or too little detail for the kind of look it’s going for. It’s absolutely just right. And while it’s not a perfect fit into Pokemon’s art style, I’d say it’s a welcome addition in the sense that it doesn’t look out of place either. It looks and feels like something you’d see out of a more heavily stylized game, like Parappa the Rappa or something.

Personal Score: 9/10

Wayyyy too fun.

Overall:

These two are without a flaw.
